{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect PLMN status reporting due to unsynchronized EPS update status\n\n### Summary\nThe NAS EMM layer was reporting incorrect network registration status because the `emm_data->stat` field was not properly synchronized with the EPS update status from USIM during initialization. This caused `emm_main_get_plmn_status()` to always return `NET_REG_STATE_OFF` regardless of the actual registration state stored in the USIM.\n\nThe issue occurred because while `emm_data->status` was correctly initialized from USIM data, the `emm_data->stat` field (which is returned by `emm_main_get_plmn_status()`) was only set to the default `NET_REG_STATE_OFF` value and never updated to reflect the actual network registration state.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/emm_main.c`: Added mapping from EPS update status to network registration status during EMM initialization to ensure `emm_data->stat` reflects the actual USIM state.\n\nUnder high load conditions when the UE attempts to retrieve registration status immediately after boot, this would cause applications to incorrectly believe the UE is not registered with the network, leading to failed connection attempts and delayed service establishment.\n"
}